
[1]temperance

   TEM'PERANCE, n. [L. temperantia, from tempero.]

   1. Moderation; particularly, habitual moderation in regard to the
   indulgence of the natural appetites and passions; restrained or
   moderate indulgence; as temperance in eating and drinking; temperance
   in the indulgence of joy or mirth. Temperance in eating and drinking is
   opposed to gluttony and drunkenness, and in other indulgences, to
   excess.

   2. Patience; calmness; sedateness; moderation of passion.

   He calm'd his wrath with goodly temperance. [Unusual.]
